description:
A specialist team within a top investment house has a vacancy for a quantitatively-orientated Portfolio Manager to manage Absolute Return and Active Equity Portfolios by means of statistical, mathematical and other numerical methodologies.
• *Key Functions**:

- Form part of the Investment Committee and quantitative team and play an active role in development and implementation of investment philosophy;
- Manage portfolios in line with mandate requirements;
- Researching, analysing and providing relevant quantitative data in support of investment decision making;
- Implement portfolio management decisions;
- Refine and enhance models and processes;
- Strong focus on internal & external relationship management with investors and other stakeholders, including some travel within SA.
• *Key Requirements**:

- Quant-orientated qualification ideally at Masters level;
- Qualified Actuary, CQF, FRM, CAIA, CFA;
- At least 10 years’ relevant experience of which 5 years must be as Portfolio Manager;
- Meet FAIS requirements;
- Well-developed quantitative and modelling skills;
- Good understanding of machine learning and deep learning methodologies;
- Market Risk experience an advantage;
- Strong programming skills in Python, Matlab or R;
- Client reporting and investment sales experience preferable;
- Excellent communication skills, (both written and presentation skills) and comfortable interacting with clients.

